    "• Tissue segmentation: it is sometimes necessary to consider the state of particular discrete portions while examining MRI images.",
    "The brain's anatomical structure removes the tissue from the target area (Lazli and Boukadoum, 2018).",
    "Measuring the tissue volume in each region is the aim of tissue segmentation.",
    "MRI was divided into three parts, and depending on the pre-treatment architecture of the CSF, white matter, and gray matter, each segment was examined alone or in combination.",
